title: ion-range
body:
The Range slider lets users select from a range of values by moving
the slider knob. It can accept dual knobs, but by default one knob
controls the value of the range.
Labels can be placed on either side of the range by adding the

to the element. The element doesn't have to
be an

, it can be added to any element to place it to the
left or right of the range.

vue: // Sets initial value for dual-knob ion-range

props.name: color
props.docs: The color to use from your application's color palette. Default options are: "primary", "secondary", "tertiary", "success", "warning", "danger", "light", "medium", and "dark". For more information on colors, see theming.

props.name: debounce
props.docs: How long, in milliseconds, to wait to trigger the ionChange event after each change in the range value.

props.name: disabled
props.docs: If true, the user cannot interact with the range.

props.name: mode
props.docs: The mode determines which platform styles to use.

props.name: name
props.docs: The name of the control, which is submitted with the form data.

props.name: pin
props.docs: If true, a pin with integer value is shown when the knob is pressed.

props.name: snaps
props.docs: If true, the knob snaps to tick marks evenly spaced based on the step property value.

props.name: ticks
props.docs: If true, tick marks are displayed based on the step value. Only applies when snaps is true.
